# GitHub API Token for Downloads Page (no longer used on the client)
#
# The downloads page fetches the latest release from the GitHub API.
# Currently, client-side GitHub tokens are NOT supported: the code
# hard-disables any client-side token usage.
#
# GitHub API rate limiting:
# - Without authentication, you're limited to 60 requests per hour.
# - For higher limits, implement a build-time or server-side fetch that
#   uses a non-VITE environment variable so the token is never exposed
#   to the browser.
#
# SECURITY NOTE:
# - Do NOT introduce new Vite (`VITE_*`) variables for secrets or tokens.
# - Any `VITE_*` value is bundled into the client and visible to all users
#   (e.g. via DevTools).
#
# This section is kept for documentation purposes only.
# There is intentionally NO `VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN` example here, because
# the downloads page no longer reads any client-side GitHub token.

